Trade points depend on the commerce of a city.
Some trade points may be lost to corruption.
The corruption of a city depends on its form of government.
The corruption of a city increases with its distance from the capitol of its civilization.
Each city distributes its remaining trade points in three ways.
Some trade points are captured as taxes.  
Taxes go into the national treasury.
Some trade points are converted into luxury points.
Luxury points influence worker morale.
Some trade points are converted to science points.
Science points contribute towards the discovery of new technology.
